HEADWORD: Pizzicato
<hw>Piz`zi*ca"to</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[It., pinched.]</ety>
<fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>A direction to violinists to pluck the string
with the finger, instead of using the bow. (Abbrev.
<abbr>pizz.</abbr>)</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

